changes.required_change:
Regenerate private/ipc/contracts/storage.py from the updated Storage contract ABI at tag v0.4.4 using web3.py contract binding tools (e.g. abi-to-python or the project's existing generation script). If regenerating is not possible, manually add the following method stubs to the generated contract wrapper class:

1. add_file_chunks(bucket_name: str, file_name: str, chunks: list[dict]) -> TxReceipt
   Each chunk dict: {"index": int (uint64), "cid": bytes, "size": int (uint256)}

2. fill_chunk_blocks(bucket_name: str, file_name: str, chunk_cid: bytes, args: list[dict]) -> TxReceipt
   Each args dict: {"block_index": int (uint8 — max 255!), "cid": bytes, "node_id": bytes (32 bytes)}
   CRITICAL: block_index is uint8 (0–255). Do NOT encode it as uint256.

3. get_block_peers_of_chunk(bucket_name: str, file_name: str, chunk_cid: bytes) -> list[dict]
   Returns list of {"cid": bytes, "node_id": bytes}

4. get_buckets_by_ids_with_files(ids: list[int]) -> list[dict]
   Returns list of {"bucket": {"name": str, "id": int, "created_at": int}, "files": [...]}

5. get_file_index_by_id(bucket_name: str, file_id: int) -> int

Also ensure the ABI JSON embedded in the file includes these error entries:
  {"type": "error", "name": "NoPeersForCID", "inputs": []}
  {"type": "error", "name": "NotEligibleToUpgrade", "inputs": []}
  {"type": "error", "name": "TooManyBlockCIDs", "inputs": []}
  {"type": "error", "name": "WrongAuthority", "inputs": []}
  {"type": "error", "name": "InvalidPeerIndex", "inputs": []}

