changes.required_change:
In sdk/sdk_ipc.py (or equivalent), ensure that any gRPC channel / connection pool used for block uploads/downloads is created once at SDK initialization and reused across Upload, Download, ArchivalMetadata, and DownloadArchival calls, rather than being created and destroyed per operation. If the Python SDK already does this (or delegates to the gRPC stub lifecycle), no change is needed.

Also note: sdk.Close() in Go now closes both the main connection AND the pool:
  func (sdk *SDK) Close() error {
    return errors.Join(sdk.conn.Close(), sdk.pool.close())
  }
If the Python SDK has a close() method, ensure it closes all managed resources.
